Figure 1. Communication Plan Definition


If Condition based is checked, you can define conditions for attaching the communication plan to matching records for the selected table. If there are no conditions, the communication plan is attached to all records for the selected table.

You can attach one or more communication plans to a major incident. Examples of communication plan definitions are:

  • Technical Communications: Collaborate with technical experts to help resolve a major incident.
  • Internal Stakeholder Communications: Keep stakeholders and business users updated on the status of a major incident.
  • End user Communications: Keep end users updated on the status of a major incident.
